  "id": "mmspanish__lesson_C2_226_regional_grammar",
  "title": "C2.226 Regional Grammar — The Many Spanishes",
  "mode": "mix_method",
  "steps": [
    {
      "phase": "english_anchor",
      "line": "In English, regional differences appear mostly in vocabulary or accent—'elevator' vs. 'lift,' 'truck' vs. 'lorry.' In Spanish, regional variation goes deeper. It changes **grammar, pronouns, and even verb conjugations.** *Vos sos mi amigo* (Argentina) becomes *Tú eres mi amigo* (Spain). *Ustedes van* replaces *vosotros vais* across Latin America. English has dialects; Spanish has **regional grammars**—each with its own rhythm and identity. English varies in word choice; Spanish varies in structure itself."
